19namespace {
20typedef absl::optional<webrtc::H265SpsParser::SpsState> OptionalSps;
21
22#define RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(x) \
23 if (!(x)) { \
24 return OptionalSps(); \
25 }
26} // namespace

28namespace webrtc {
29
30H265SpsParser::SpsState::SpsState() = default;
31
32// General note: this is based off the 02/2018 version of the H.265 standard.
33// You can find it on this page:
34// http://www.itu.int/rec/T-REC-H.265
35
36// Unpack RBSP and parse SPS state from the supplied buffer.
37absl::optional<H265SpsParser::SpsState> H265SpsParser::ParseSps(
38 const uint8_t* data,
39 size_t length) {
40 std::vector<uint8_t> unpacked_buffer = H265::ParseRbsp(data, length);
41 rtc::BitBuffer bit_buffer(unpacked_buffer.data(), unpacked_buffer.size());
42 return ParseSpsUpToVui(&bit_buffer);
43}
44
45absl::optional<H265SpsParser::SpsState> H265SpsParser::ParseSpsUpToVui(
46 rtc::BitBuffer* buffer) {
47 // Now, we need to use a bit buffer to parse through the actual HEVC SPS
48 // format. See Section 7.3.2.2.1 ("General sequence parameter set data
49 // syntax") of the H.265 standard for a complete description.
50 // Since we only care about resolution, we ignore the majority of fields, but
51 // we still have to actively parse through a lot of the data, since many of
52 // the fields have variable size.
53 // We're particularly interested in:
54 // chroma_format_idc -> affects crop units
55 // pic_{width,height}_* -> resolution of the frame in macroblocks (16x16).
56 // frame_crop_*_offset -> crop information
57
58 SpsState sps;
59
60 // The golomb values we have to read, not just consume.
61 uint32_t golomb_ignored;
62
63 // separate_colour_plane_flag is optional (assumed 0), but has implications
64 // about the ChromaArrayType, which modifies how we treat crop coordinates.
65 uint32_t separate_colour_plane_flag = 0;
66
67 // chroma_format_idc will be ChromaArrayType if separate_colour_plane_flag is
68 // 0. It defaults to 1, when not specified.
69 uint32_t chroma_format_idc = 1;
70
71 // sps_video_parameter_set_id: u(4)
72 uint32_t sps_video_parameter_set_id = 0;
73 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadBits(&sps_video_parameter_set_id, 4));
74 // sps_max_sub_layers_minus1: u(3)
75 uint32_t sps_max_sub_layers_minus1 = 0;
76 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadBits(&sps_max_sub_layers_minus1, 3));
77 // sps_temporal_id_nesting_flag: u(1)
78 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ConsumeBits(1));
79 // profile_tier_level(1, sps_max_sub_layers_minus1). We are acutally not
80 // using them, so read/skip over it.
81 // general_profile_space+general_tier_flag+general_prfile_idc: u(8)
82 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ConsumeBytes(1));
83 // general_profile_compatabilitiy_flag[32]
84 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ConsumeBytes(4));
85 // general_progressive_source_flag + interlaced_source_flag+
86 // non-packed_constraint flag + frame_only_constraint_flag: u(4)
87 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ConsumeBits(4));
88 // general_profile_idc decided flags or reserved. u(43)
89 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ConsumeBits(43));
90 // general_inbld_flag or reserved 0: u(1)
91 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ConsumeBits(1));
92 // general_level_idc: u(8)
93 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ConsumeBytes(1));
94 // if max_sub_layers_minus1 >=1, read the sublayer profile information
95 std::vector<uint32_t> sub_layer_profile_present_flags;
96 std::vector<uint32_t> sub_layer_level_present_flags;
97 uint32_t sub_layer_profile_present = 0;
98 uint32_t sub_layer_level_present = 0;
99 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < sps_max_sub_layers_minus1; i++) {
100 // sublayer_profile_present_flag and sublayer_level_presnet_flag: u(2)
101 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadBits(&sub_layer_profile_present, 1));
102 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadBits(&sub_layer_level_present, 1));
103 sub_layer_profile_present_flags.push_back(sub_layer_profile_present);
104 sub_layer_level_present_flags.push_back(sub_layer_level_present);
105 }
106 if (sps_max_sub_layers_minus1 > 0) {
107 for (uint32_t j = sps_max_sub_layers_minus1; j < 8; j++) {
108 // reserved 2 bits: u(2)
109 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ConsumeBits(2));
110 }
111 }
112 for (uint32_t k = 0; k < sps_max_sub_layers_minus1; k++) {
113 if (sub_layer_profile_present_flags[k]) { //
114 // sub_layer profile_space/tier_flag/profile_idc. ignored. u(8)
115 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ConsumeBytes(1));
116 // profile_compatability_flag: u(32)
117 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ConsumeBytes(4));
118 // sub_layer progressive_source_flag/interlaced_source_flag/
119 // non_packed_constraint_flag/frame_only_constraint_flag: u(4)
120 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ConsumeBits(4));
121 // following 43-bits are profile_idc specific. We simply read/skip it.
122 // u(43)
123 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ConsumeBits(43));
124 // 1-bit profile_idc specific inbld flag. We simply read/skip it. u(1)
125 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ConsumeBits(1));
126 }
127 if (sub_layer_level_present_flags[k]) {
128 // sub_layer_level_idc: u(8)
129 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ConsumeBytes(1));
130 }
131 }
132 // sps_seq_parameter_set_id: ue(v)
133 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(&golomb_ignored));
134 // chrome_format_idc: ue(v)
135 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(&chroma_format_idc));
136 if (chroma_format_idc == 3) {
137 // seperate_colour_plane_flag: u(1)
138 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadBits(&separate_colour_plane_flag, 1));
139 }
140 uint32_t pic_width_in_luma_samples = 0;
141 uint32_t pic_height_in_luma_samples = 0;
142 // pic_width_in_luma_samples: ue(v)
143 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
144 buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(&pic_width_in_luma_samples));
145 // pic_height_in_luma_samples: ue(v)
146 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
147 buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(&pic_height_in_luma_samples));
148 // conformance_window_flag: u(1)
149 uint32_t conformance_window_flag = 0;
150 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadBits(&conformance_window_flag, 1));
151
152 uint32_t conf_win_left_offset = 0;
153 uint32_t conf_win_right_offset = 0;
154 uint32_t conf_win_top_offset = 0;
155 uint32_t conf_win_bottom_offset = 0;
156 if (conformance_window_flag) {
157 // conf_win_left_offset: ue(v)
158 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(&conf_win_left_offset));
159 // conf_win_right_offset: ue(v)
160 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(&conf_win_right_offset));
161 // conf_win_top_offset: ue(v)
162 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(&conf_win_top_offset));
163 // conf_win_bottom_offset: ue(v)
164 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
165 buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(&conf_win_bottom_offset));
166 }
167
168 // Far enough! We don't use the rest of the SPS.
169
170 sps.vps_id = sps_video_parameter_set_id;
171
172 // Start with the resolution determined by the pic_width/pic_height fields.
173 sps.width = pic_width_in_luma_samples;
174 sps.height = pic_height_in_luma_samples;
175
176 if (conformance_window_flag) {
177 int sub_width_c = ((1 == chroma_format_idc) || (2 == chroma_format_idc)) &&
178 (0 == separate_colour_plane_flag)
179 ? 2
180 : 1;
181 int sub_height_c =
182 (1 == chroma_format_idc) && (0 == separate_colour_plane_flag) ? 2 : 1;
183 // the offset includes the pixel within conformance window. so don't need to
184 // +1 as per spec
185 sps.width -= sub_width_c * (conf_win_right_offset + conf_win_left_offset);
186 sps.height -= sub_height_c * (conf_win_top_offset + conf_win_bottom_offset);
187 }
188
189 return OptionalSps(sps);
190}
